<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-06T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="206" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">875.01/11–144: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to Mr. <persName type="to">Alexander C.
                                        Kirk</persName>, Political Adviser, Allied Force
                                    Headquarters at Caserta</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-06T16:00:00-04:00">November 6, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>346. The Department hopes that you will continue to keep it informed
                                regarding developments in Albania. We should like particularly to
                                have any details that may come to your attention regarding the
                                circumstances surrounding the resignation of the Tirana Government
                                and the extent to which FNC has established its authority over the
                                country.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>